OL,7,FBut she did not have anorexia, she has
OL,8,FARFID, a disorder where people are
OL,9,Fsimply not interested in food. Ms
OL,10,FMacpherson says she finds the sensory
OL,11,Faspects of eating and preparing food
OL,12,F"repulsive".
OL,14,FARFID (avoidant restrictive food
OL,15,Fintake disorder) was first recognised
OL,16,Fin 2013, and is often linked to autism.
OL,18,FBut in 2024 there has been a "dramatic
OL,19,Fincrease" in cases, according to
OL,20,Feating disorder charity Beat.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G2/15
